    "created_at": "2023-12-12T09:35:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-12-12T09:35:57Z",
    "body": "`exec` **replaces** your current shell with the command specified. Because `starship` without any further arguments just prints the usage info and then exists, `exec starship` is basically the same as typing `echo \"usage info\"; exit`.\r\n\r\nWhat likely happened is that you started in a root shell, switched to your user using `su bf` and then just exited the user shell, which places you right back in the root shell. Nothing related to starship at all.",
